    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_75_1828_05_06_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline> 
                        <note>9</note>
                        <note>40</note>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                        <date when="1828-05-06">May 6. <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1828</date></dateline></opener>
                
                <p>
                 
                    My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">friend</persName> You think you<lb/>
                    have got rid of me - &amp; all of us<lb/>
                    by calling us the most <choice><orig>amia-<lb/>
                    ble</orig><reg>amiable</reg></choice> family you have ever<lb/>
                    known. - But you are <choice><orig>mis=<lb/>
                    taken</orig><reg>mistaken</reg></choice> my good friend - not<lb/>
                    in your assertion - but in<lb/>
                    your hope of having got clear<lb/>
                    rid of your visit to this most<lb/>
                    amiable family you have<lb/>
                    ever known -<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    For how unhappy flatterer<lb/>
                    you are going to be put to the<lb/>
                    test - An opportunity occurs<lb/>
                    - (Oh how you groan inwardly)<lb/>
                    of bringing you over to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName><lb/>
                    the first week in June - in a<lb/>
                    gentleman's carriage, - so that<lb/>
                    you would have no difficulty<lb/>
                    about means of conveyance<lb/>
                    &amp; you would <add>not</add> have the misery<lb/>
                    which you dread of travelling<lb/>
                    
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_75_1828_05_06_page02.jpg"/>
                    - The gentleman is the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParsW1" cert="high">Lord<lb/>
                    Rosse</persName> - now in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> at<lb/>
                    Millers hotel <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Jermyn-Street_ENK">Jermyn Street</placeName><lb/>
                    - He could bring you over<lb/>
                    to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName> and lodge you<lb/>
                    at the house of an aunt &amp;<lb/>
                    sister of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Edgeworths</persName> and<lb/>
                    there either i or some of my<lb/>
                    family who will be in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName><lb/>
                    at that time would find you<lb/>
                    &amp; bring you down here<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    As to the means of your<lb/>
                    going back again I have not<lb/>
                    yet contrived those - but the<lb/>
                    present specimen of my <choice><orig>con-<lb/>
                    =trivance</orig><reg>contrivance</reg></choice> ought to give you<lb/>
                    such confidence in my <choice><orig>re-<lb/>
                    sources</orig><reg>resources</reg></choice> as to make you trust<lb/>
                    to my promise that you shall<lb/>
                    
                    <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_75_1828_05_06_page03.jpg"/>
                    <note>41</note>
                    not be left to perish here in the<lb/>
                    center of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName> (in the<lb/>
                    midst of your friends) but<lb/>
                    that you shall be conveyed<lb/>
                    in some safe and agreeable<lb/>
                    manner &amp; with some <choice><orig>support<lb/>
                    =able</orig><reg>supportable</reg></choice> travelling companion to<lb/>
                    <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> again if you please -<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    I have only a moment<lb/>
                    to throw my thoughts before<lb/>
                    you - Answer me directly<lb/>
                    - Whether you <hi rend="underline">can</hi>- or rather<lb/>
                    Whether will come or not &amp;<lb/>
                    Then I will write to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParsW1" cert="high">Lord<lb/>
                    Rosse</persName> &amp; learn his possibilities<lb/>
                    precisely -<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                    Consider the dilemma to<lb/>
                    which you have reduced<lb/>
                    yourself!<lb/></p>
                    <closer>I am my d<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> friend y<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> truly - rejoicing<lb/>
                    in your discomfiture<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria <damage>Edgeworth</damage></persName><lb/></closer>
                    
                    <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_75_1828_05_06_page04.jpg"/>
                    <postscript><p>
                    Your picture of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LansH1">Lord</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LansL1">Lady<lb/>
                    Lansdowne</persName> is beautiful &amp;<lb/>
                    just -<lb/></p>
                    </postscript>
                
                <closer>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine/>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">a Monsieur</persName>
                        <addrLine/>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DumoE1">Monsieur Dumont</persName>
                    </address></closer>
                
